external_knowledge:
- "castles" metaphorically refers to "servers" in the context of the database;
- "knights who rule" metaphorically refers to the "users" who have a significant role in the server's activities (in this case, setting the channel topic);
- "halls" are a metaphor for "channels" within the server environment;
- "carved their emblems into the stone" symbolizes "setting the topic" for a channel.

sql:
SELECT channels.channel_name, channel_modes.mode
FROM channels
INNER JOIN channel_modes ON channels.channel_id = channel_modes.channel_id;

SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM irc_commands
WHERE command = 'RPL_WELCOME';
